ing the restructuring of the [[Big East Conference (1979\u20132013)|Big East Conference]]. The awards existed in the same format in the Big East from 1991 to 2012.\n\nThe five awards include Offensive Player of the Year, Defensive Player of the Year, Special Teams Player of the Year, Rookie of the Year, and Coach of the Year. Recipients are selected by the votes of the conference's head coaches.<ref name=\"2013list\">{{cite web |url=http://theamerican.org/news/2013/12/11/FB_1211130338.aspx |title=American Athletic Conference Announces 2013 Postseason Football Honors |date=December 11, 2013 |author=American Athletic Conference |accessdate=December 31, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Offensive Player of the Year==\nThe Offensive Player of the Year is awarded to the player voted most outstanding at an offensive position.\n\n===Winners===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|style=\"background-color:#FFE6BD; width:3em;\" |*\n|Unanimous selection\n|-\n|style=\"background-color:#CFECEC; width:3em;\" |<sup>\u2020</sup>\n|Co-Player of the Year\n|-\n|Player (X)\n|Denotes the number of times the player has been selected\n|}\n{|class=wikitable\n!colspan=8|Positions key\n|-\n| '''QB''' || [[Quarterback]]\n| '''RB''' || [[Running back]]\n| '''TE''' || [[Tight end]]\n| '''WR''' || [[Wide receiver]]\n|-\n!colspan=8|Class key\n|-\n|'''Fr''' || Freshman\n|'''So''' || Sophomore\n|'''Jr''' || Junior\n|'''Sr''' || Senior\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Season\n!Player\n!School\n!Position\n!Class\n|- align=center\n| [[2013 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2013]] || {{sortname|Blake|Bortles}} || [[2013 UCF Knights football team|UCF]] || QB || {{sort|3|Jr}}\n|- align=center\n| [[2014 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2014]] || {{sortname|Shane|Carden}}<ref name=\"2014 awards\">{{cite press release|url=http://theamerican.org/news/2014/12/10/FB_1210143903.aspx |title=American Athletic Conference Announces 2014 Postseason Football Honors |publisher=American Athletic Conference |date=December 10, 2014