A World Factbook</ref> || 42,300<ref group=\"n\">2010 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref>\n|-\n| \u2014 ||''{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} {{flagicon|Falkland Islands}} [[Economy of the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]]''<ref group=\"n\">The Falkland Islands are an [[British Overseas Territories|overseas territory]] of the [[United Kingdom]].</ref> || 281.8<ref group=\"n\">2012 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref> || 96,200<ref group=\"n\">2012 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref>\n|-\n| \u2014 ||''{{flagicon|New Zealand}} {{flagicon|Cook Islands}} [[Economy of the Cook Islands|Cook Islands]]''<ref group=\"n\">The Cook Islands are in free association with [[New Zealand]].</ref> || 244.1<ref group=\"n\">2013 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref> || 12,300<ref group=\"n\">2010 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref>\n|-\n| 51 ||{{flagicon|Kiribati}} [[Economy of Kiribati|Kiribati]] || 250 || 1,866\n|-\n| \u2014 ||''{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} {{flagicon|Anguilla}} [[Economy of Anguilla|Anguilla]]''<ref group=\"n\">Anguilla is an [[British Overseas Territories|overseas territory]] of the [[United Kingdom]].</ref> || 175.4<ref group=\"n\">2009 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref> || 12,200<ref group=\"n\">2008 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref>\n|-\n| 52 ||{{flagicon|Nauru}} [[Economy of Nauru|Nauru]] || 117 || 7,856\n|-\n| \u2014 ||''{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} {{flagicon|Montserrat}} [[Economy of Montserrat|Montserrat]]''<ref group=\"n\">Montserrat is an [[British Overseas Territories|overseas territory]] of the [[United Kingdom]].</ref> || 43.8<ref group=\"n\">2006 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref> || 8,500<ref group=\"n\">2006 estimate from the CIA World Factbook</ref>\n|-\n| 53 ||{{flagicon|Tuvalu}} [[Economy of Tuvalu|Tuvalu]] || 47 || 3,734\n|-\n| \u2014 ||''{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} {{flagicon|Saint Helena}} {{flagicon|Ascension}} {{flagicon|Tristan da Cunha}} [[Economy of Saint Helena|Saint Helena]], [[Ascensio